The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network model for ordinal regression, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model is applied to image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of loss functions and statistical analysis, which are common in the fields of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
